<p><big><b>S</b></big>o, you've heard about the newest craze for buying and selling online: <a href="http://www.bitcoin.org">bitcoin</a>. For the first time in history we have a cash-like currency for online transactions. It's instant, anonymous and irreversible. How do you get some so you can go buy <a href="http://www.bitcoin.org/trade">some of the products or services available through bitcoin?</a></p>

<p>For small transactions you can use <a href="http://coinpal.ndrix.com/">CoinPal</a>. But this is only an option if you don&#39;t mind limiting yourself to 20 BTC total purchase per-week. And it requires a verified PayPal account, something many people don&#39;t have or know how to get. What then? How can you buy some Bitcoin?</p>

