<p>No matter what method you choose to send money you will always have the following problems.</p>

<ol>
  <li>You don&#39;t know if the person you&#39;re sending money to is <b>trustworthy</b>.</li>
  <li>You have no way of <b>verifying</b> that your exchange partner owns bitcoins to trade with you.</li>
  <li>If you send Western Union, Moneygram, FedEx, UPS or postal mail you have no way to prove that the money was <b>received</b> by your exchange partner.</li>
  <li>There is no way to buy bitcoins <b>today</b> that costs less than $15 USD minimum.</li>
</ol>

